Metadata: Egregiachloride​s A-C: new chlorinated oxylipins from the marine brown alga "Egregia menziesii"

Three new chlorinated and carbocyclic oxylipins as well as one olefin analog were isolated from the temperate brown alga "Egregia menziesii" along with the previously reported ecklonialactone​s A, B and E. A biogenesis of the egregiachloride​s is proposed which is initiated by lipoxygenation followed by cyclization and termination by chloride of an omega3 carbocation.
